* Telco lauded for appreciating dealers Top business partners of foremost digital services company, Globacom, were on Friday celebrated at the exquisite 2022 Dealers Appreciation Gala Dinner where the company announced over N750m worth of rewards for them in appreciation of their past support, whilst looking forward to a more mutually beneficial partnership in the future.The event which was held at the Eko Hotels and Suites in Lagos was attended by the company’s business associates from all over the country as well as Management and staff of Globacom.In his address, the Chairman of Globacom Dr. Mike Adenuga Jr who was represented by Retail & Consumer Sales Chief, Globacom, Mr. Ken Ogujiofor, said the event was organized to celebrate Glo’s business partners who had worked assiduously with the company in its  quest to make Globacom the number one Telecommunications and Digital services provider in Nigeria.He explained that the event was a continuation of Glo’s tradition of rewarding and upholding excellence among its treasured partners, adding that In the last quarter of 2021, Globacom announced a special incentive by its Chairman to bolster the distribution business and encourage its partners to strive even higher to meet the business goals of the company.“We are delighted to note that the reward programme was a huge success, with many of our partners achieving and surpassing the target bands set for the two categories; volume push and activations. Very shortly, we shall be presenting prizes to the winners from different parts of the country”, he explained.In his presentation at the ceremony, Mr. Viju Unnithan of Marketing Department, Globacom highlighted the company’s commitment to enhancing Customer value, adding that the company’s product and services were packaged to add value to Glo subscribers, while another presentation by Mr. Remi Makinde of Globacom’s Network Implementation Group, dwelled extensively on the company’s Network Quality Enhancement plan and how it has boosted the network significantly.The overwhelmed dealers were effusive in their praise of Globacom which rewarded different categories of its dealers with cash prizes in form of credit notes running into millions of naira, in addition to other incentives.“Globacom has delighted its trade partners tonight and on behalf of my fellow dealers, we say thank you to Globacom” said Managing Director of Zeph Associates, Mr. Tochukwu Nwosu whose company carted home three top prizes among the category 1dealers.Also another winner, the Managing Director of Yarab Integrated Limited, Alhaji Mobolaji Abdulrasaq said Globacom’s gesture was truly appreciated. “We will continue to work towards the progress of the company. Kudos to Glo.”In the same vein, CEO of Alenssar Infinity Communication Chief Edward Emeano, also a winner, expressed his joy on the way Globacom appreciated its business partners. According to him, “Globacom has showed its true appreciation of our efforts in marketing the company’s products and services and we are truly grateful”It was an evening of fun and entertainment as top musicians and comedians including  juju maestro, King Sunny Ade (KSA) and his African beats, the Groove Band and the duo of Godwin Komone aka Gordons and MC Forever treated the guests to vintage music, comedy and wise cracks with guests enjoying every bit of the evening.